            <drmd:description>
               <dcc:content lang="en">Reference material BAM-U026 was obtained by blending a sandy loamy soil from a contaminated site in Berlin, Germany with a TPH free sandy loamy soil sampled near Berlin, Germany. After air-drying, sieving fractions &lt; 125 µm were mixed, homogenized, and subdivided into 70 g which were filled in amber glass bottles with screw caps equipped with PTFE-inserts and sealed with shrinking foil. The material is stored at BAM at -20 °C until dispatch. Details of the preparation and characterization procedures are specified in the certification report.</dcc:content>
